ep water. The Spirit of God was hovering over the water."}, {:version=>"JPS Tanakh 1917", :text=>"Now the earth was unformed and void, and darkness was upon the face of the deep; and the spirit of God hovered over the face of the waters."}, {:version=>"New American Standard 1977 ", :text=>"And the earth was formless and void, and darkness was over the surface of the deep; and the Spirit of God was moving over the surface of the waters."}, {:version=>"King James 2000 Bible", :text=>"And the earth was without form, and void; and darkness was upon the face of the deep. And the Spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters."}, {:version=>"American King James Version", :text=>"And the earth was without form, and void; and darkness was on the face of the deep. And the Spirit of God moved on the face of the waters."}, {:version=>"American Standard Version", :text=>"And the earth was waste and void; and darkness was upon the face of the deep: and the Spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters."}, {:version=>"Brenton Septuagint Translation", :text=>"But the earth was unsightly and unfurnished, and darkness was over the deep, and the Spirit of God moved over the water."}, {:version=>"Douay-Rheims Bible", :text=>"And the earth was void and empty, and darkness was upon the face of the deep; and the spirit of God moved over the waters. "}, {:version=>"Darby Bible Translation", :text=>"And the earth was waste and empty, and darkness was on the face of the deep, and the Spirit of God was hovering over the face of the waters."}, {:version=>"English Revised Version", :text=>"And the earth was waste and void; and darkness was upon the face of the deep: and the spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters."}, {:version=>"Webster's Bible Translation", :text=>"And the earth was without form, and void; and darkness was upon the face of the deep: and the Spirit of God moved upon the face of the waters."}, {:version=>"World English Bible", :text=>"Now the earth was formless and empty. Darkness was on the surface of the deep. God's Spirit was hovering over the surface of the waters."}, {:version=>"Young's Literal Translation", :text=>" the earth hath existed waste and void, and darkness is on the face of the deep, and the Spirit of God fluttering on the face of the waters,"}]}